WEBVTT

00:01:35.467 --> 00:01:37.166
[GASPS]
Renji.

00:01:40.734 --> 00:01:41.934
Renji!

00:01:41.934 --> 00:01:43.700
Why, why'd you do it?

00:01:43.700 --> 00:01:45.467
Renji!

00:01:48.867 --> 00:01:50.567
Huh?

00:01:55.133 --> 00:01:56.400
[GASPS]

00:01:56.400 --> 00:01:58.300
Good morning.

00:01:58.300 --> 00:02:01.433
How are you today, Rukia dear?

00:02:01.433 --> 00:02:03.233
Ichimaru.

00:02:03.233 --> 00:02:05.433
Gin.

00:02:08.800 --> 00:02:11.300
ICHIMARU:
Such bad manners, Rukia.

00:02:11.300 --> 00:02:14.367
But I see you are just
the same as you always were.

00:02:14.367 --> 00:02:15.967
Still rude.

00:02:15.967 --> 00:02:18.600
You know, you must
always address me only

00:02:18.600 --> 00:02:20.233
as Captain Ichimaru.

00:02:20.233 --> 00:02:23.567
If you're not careful,
you may get a serious scolding

00:02:23.567 --> 00:02:26.834
from your brother, Byakuyu.

00:02:26.834 --> 00:02:30.433
I apologize, Captain Ichimaru.

00:02:30.433 --> 00:02:32.633
[LAUGHS]
Oh, no.

00:02:32.633 --> 00:02:34.333
Did you think I was serious?

00:02:34.333 --> 00:02:35.667
Don't worry.

00:02:35.667 --> 00:02:37.400
I'm about to turn you in.

00:02:37.400 --> 00:02:38.867
I really don't even mind,

00:02:38.867 --> 00:02:41.266
since you and I have known
each other for so long.

00:02:41.266 --> 00:02:44.367
I know that you didn't come
by to make small talk, Captain.

00:02:44.367 --> 00:02:46.867
Tell me, why are you here?

00:02:46.867 --> 00:02:51.300
Well, I suppose no
particular reason, Rukia.

00:02:51.300 --> 00:02:54.166
I was out taking
a walk and thought I'd visit,

00:02:54.166 --> 00:02:56.800
just to tease you a little bit.

00:02:59.734 --> 00:03:03.266
RUKIA:
I never liked this man.

00:03:03.266 --> 00:03:04.667
The first time we met

00:03:04.667 --> 00:03:07.633
was before I joined
the 13 Court Guard Squads,

00:03:07.633 --> 00:03:11.133
just after my brother
was made captain of Squad Six.

00:03:11.133 --> 00:03:15.066
Gin became captain of Squad
Three about the same time.

00:03:15.066 --> 00:03:17.667
And I remember him
chatting with Byakuyu

00:03:17.667 --> 00:03:20.633
whenever they happened to meet.

00:03:20.633 --> 00:03:23.066
It didn't look like anything
other than two captains

00:03:23.066 --> 00:03:25.000
exchanging pleasantries.

00:03:25.000 --> 00:03:27.467
There was never anything
of any substance said.

00:03:27.467 --> 00:03:29.934
So to an outsider,
they would have seemed

00:03:29.934 --> 00:03:32.000
like normal conversations.

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:35.533
But they never seemed
that way to me.

00:03:35.533 --> 00:03:39.100
From the first time
I laid eyes on this man,

00:03:39.100 --> 00:03:42.600
I broke out in a cold
sweat all over my body.

00:03:42.600 --> 00:03:45.066
His fingertips,
his lips,

00:03:45.066 --> 00:03:47.133
the way his eyes narrowed
and shifted,

00:03:47.133 --> 00:03:49.767
he reminded me of a snake.

00:03:49.767 --> 00:03:52.133
And though he was
speaking to my brother,

00:03:52.133 --> 00:03:55.133
I felt as if he had his
hands around my neck.

00:03:55.133 --> 00:03:59.100
I was frozen,
afraid even to blink my eyes.

00:03:59.100 --> 00:04:02.033
I've always hated this man.

00:04:02.033 --> 00:04:04.633
It seemed like he could find
the smallest crack

00:04:04.633 --> 00:04:06.000
in those around him

00:04:06.000 --> 00:04:09.567
and seep deep down into you,
like venom.

00:04:09.567 --> 00:04:12.233
That's the kind of
fear he arouses.

00:04:12.233 --> 00:04:16.166
I've never had any rational
reason for feeling this way.

00:04:16.166 --> 00:04:18.200
But something
inside me has always

00:04:18.200 --> 00:04:20.233
rejected everything about him.

00:04:20.233 --> 00:04:23.467
Despite the many times
we've spoken over the years,

00:04:23.467 --> 00:04:26.133
those feelings
have never changed.

00:04:26.133 --> 00:04:29.834
Even now, I still feel
that way about him.

00:04:29.834 --> 00:04:32.333
ICHIMARU:
What's the matter?

00:04:32.333 --> 00:04:35.834
It seems you fell
into a trance there.

00:04:35.834 --> 00:04:38.567
Sort of.

00:04:38.567 --> 00:04:42.200
By the way, seems he
isn't actually dead yet.

00:04:42.200 --> 00:04:43.700
Renji, that is.

00:04:43.700 --> 00:04:46.700
[GASPS]

00:04:46.700 --> 00:04:48.633
RUKIA:
It's true.

00:04:48.633 --> 00:04:50.867
I have to concentrate
and search,

00:04:50.867 --> 00:04:54.033
but I can still sense
Renji's spiritual pressure.

00:04:54.033 --> 00:04:56.433
But it's so weak.

00:04:56.433 --> 00:05:00.000
But he will die soon.

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:02.000
It's kind of pathetic.

00:05:02.000 --> 00:05:05.133
He tried to save your life,
but he just got cut to pieces.

00:05:05.133 --> 00:05:07.767
Don't you dare
make light of him!

00:05:09.600 --> 00:05:11.300
Are you afraid?

00:05:11.300 --> 00:05:13.633
Afraid? Of what?

00:05:13.633 --> 00:05:15.467
You don't want
Renji and the others

00:05:15.467 --> 00:05:17.834
to die trying to
rescue you, do you?

00:05:17.834 --> 00:05:19.533
Knowing they're
trying to save you

00:05:19.533 --> 00:05:21.734
must make this all
the more painful.

00:05:25.467 --> 00:05:27.834
Want me to save you?

00:05:27.834 --> 00:05:30.000
Ca-- Captain Ichimaru.

00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:32.266
You don't mean it.
What are you saying, sir?

00:05:32.266 --> 00:05:35.000
I could rescue you
from this execution

00:05:35.000 --> 00:05:38.934
and save your life right now.
You and Renji,

00:05:38.934 --> 00:05:40.433
and the others too.

00:05:42.800 --> 00:05:44.333
RUKIA:
Is he serious?

00:05:44.333 --> 00:05:47.233
What could he possibly
have to gain by saving me?

00:05:47.233 --> 00:05:49.000
There's even less
reason for him

00:05:49.000 --> 00:05:51.500
to want to save Ichigo
and Renji.

00:05:51.500 --> 00:05:53.800
Why would he say such a thing?

00:05:53.800 --> 00:05:56.567
You think I'm kidding?

00:05:58.066 --> 00:05:59.734
I am.

00:06:02.433 --> 00:06:03.834
Bye bye, Rukia.

00:06:03.834 --> 00:06:06.433
I'll see once more
at the Sokyoku.

00:06:06.433 --> 00:06:10.233
RUKIA:
I can't believe
I let him do that to me.

00:06:10.233 --> 00:06:13.266
After I had abandoned
all hope,

00:06:13.266 --> 00:06:16.367
accepted my fate 
and my impending death,

00:06:16.367 --> 00:06:18.934
he was able
to shake my resolve.

00:06:18.934 --> 00:06:21.633
By holding out that
small sliver of hope,

00:06:21.633 --> 00:06:25.200
he managed to make
me yearn just a bit.

00:06:25.200 --> 00:06:27.633
He made me want to live again.

00:06:27.633 --> 00:06:32.300
How could he have shattered
my strength so easily?

00:06:32.300 --> 00:06:35.300
[SCREAMS]

00:06:42.100 --> 00:06:43.633
Hm?
Huh?

00:06:43.633 --> 00:06:45.867
KENPACHI:
Don't let your guard down.

00:06:45.867 --> 00:06:48.000
You make it too easy for me.

00:06:49.467 --> 00:06:50.967
Kaname!

00:06:50.967 --> 00:06:54.000
What are you looking
around for, idiot?

00:06:57.767 --> 00:06:59.800
This is ridiculous.

00:06:59.800 --> 00:07:02.200
How did the two of you
ever become captains

00:07:02.200 --> 00:07:03.767
in the first place?

00:07:03.767 --> 00:07:05.300
Come on and stand up.

00:07:05.300 --> 00:07:07.467
You don't look to me
like you're dead yet.

00:07:07.467 --> 00:07:11.166
At least die like a captain
and release your Bankai first.

00:07:11.166 --> 00:07:14.066
What would you know
of a captain's honor, traitor?

00:07:14.066 --> 00:07:16.400
You're not even
worthy of Bankai.

00:07:16.400 --> 00:07:18.433
TOSEN:
Hold it, Sajin.

00:07:18.433 --> 00:07:21.834
Leave this to me.

00:07:23.233 --> 00:07:25.467
There are three ways
to become a captain

00:07:25.467 --> 00:07:27.567
in the 13 Court Guard Squads.

00:07:27.567 --> 00:07:30.767
The first is to pass
the captain's exam,

00:07:30.767 --> 00:07:32.934
presided over by three
other captains,

00:07:32.934 --> 00:07:35.867
including the head captain
himself.

00:07:35.867 --> 00:07:38.066
The second is to receive
the recommendation

00:07:38.066 --> 00:07:40.567
of six or more captains
and be acknowledged

00:07:40.567 --> 00:07:43.934
by at least three of
the remaining seven captains.

00:07:43.934 --> 00:07:46.667
The only other way is to
defeat the previous captain

00:07:46.667 --> 00:07:48.133
in a one-on-one battle,

00:07:48.133 --> 00:07:52.100
which must be witnessed
by 200 or more squad members.

00:07:52.100 --> 00:07:53.934
[LAUGHS]
So what's your point?

00:07:53.934 --> 00:07:56.533
Ever since the moment you
killed the former captain

00:07:56.533 --> 00:07:59.900
of Squad 11 and replaced
him with Kenpachi Zaraki,

00:07:59.900 --> 00:08:03.033
I felt a deep unease
about you,

00:08:03.033 --> 00:08:05.533
unease that has become
a certainty.

00:08:05.533 --> 00:08:07.567
A certainty that you're a demon,

00:08:07.567 --> 00:08:09.934
that you thrive
on violence and blood,

00:08:09.934 --> 00:08:12.400
that you're different
from the rest of us.

00:08:12.400 --> 00:08:15.033
And a certainty that
you are bound someday

00:08:15.033 --> 00:08:16.633
to destroy the peace.

00:08:16.633 --> 00:08:20.467
And sure enough, now you
have saved the Ryoka.

00:08:20.467 --> 00:08:22.567
And here you fight against us,

00:08:22.567 --> 00:08:26.300
threatening to bring even more
chaos to the Seiretei.

00:08:26.300 --> 00:08:29.767
And it's all because of
your insatiable bloodlust

00:08:29.767 --> 00:08:31.800
and your love of fighting
for its own sake.

00:08:31.800 --> 00:08:33.200
Am I wrong?

00:08:33.200 --> 00:08:35.266
I don't know about
right or wrong.

00:08:35.266 --> 00:08:37.066
But I can see you sure
have a problem

00:08:37.066 --> 00:08:38.800
when it comes to getting
to the point.

00:08:38.800 --> 00:08:40.467
Enough babbling.

00:08:40.467 --> 00:08:43.700
If you hate me so much, then
there's no need for speeches.

00:08:43.700 --> 00:08:45.734
Just shut up and
attack me already.

00:08:45.734 --> 00:08:46.934
No hatred.

00:08:46.934 --> 00:08:50.433
I never actually said that
I hated you, Kenpachi.

00:08:50.433 --> 00:08:52.800
I simply find you unforgivable!

00:08:52.800 --> 00:08:55.133
Everything you do
threatens the peace

00:08:55.133 --> 00:08:57.834
we have worked so hard
to establish here.

00:08:57.834 --> 00:08:59.467
So in the name of justice,

00:08:59.467 --> 00:09:02.266
I now have no choice
but to erase you.

00:09:02.266 --> 00:09:04.467
Kaname.

00:09:12.100 --> 00:09:13.567
Bankai.

00:09:29.066 --> 00:09:33.033
Suzumushi Tsushiki, Emma Korogi.

00:09:36.000 --> 00:09:38.433
So you wanted to see my Bankai?

00:09:38.433 --> 00:09:39.700
This is it.

00:09:39.700 --> 00:09:42.900
This entire space
is now my Bankai.

00:09:42.900 --> 00:09:47.867
So tell me, Kenpachi Zaraki,

00:09:47.867 --> 00:09:50.233
what do you think?

00:09:51.767 --> 00:09:55.233
You can see nothing
and hear nothing.

00:09:55.233 --> 00:09:56.867
KENPACHI:
What is this?

00:09:56.867 --> 00:09:58.166
I can't see.

00:09:58.166 --> 00:10:00.367
And I can't hear a sound.

00:10:02.166 --> 00:10:04.467
Do you find it
a little frightening,

00:10:04.467 --> 00:10:07.066
a world without sight or sound?

00:10:07.066 --> 00:10:10.333
The Emma Korogi steals
all spiritual pressure,

00:10:10.333 --> 00:10:13.133
all perceptions and
senses of those within it,

00:10:13.133 --> 00:10:17.533
and creates in their
place a dark, silent hell.

00:10:17.533 --> 00:10:20.600
There is only one man
who can escape this hell,

00:10:20.600 --> 00:10:23.600
and that is he who
wields Suzumushi.

00:10:26.567 --> 00:10:28.133
It's useless.

00:10:28.133 --> 00:10:30.934
You are far too
slow to counter me.

00:10:30.934 --> 00:10:32.800
No matter how
skilled one may be,

00:10:32.800 --> 00:10:35.567
when deprived of light so
suddenly, it is the end.

00:10:35.567 --> 00:10:38.400
With the sudden darkness,
a tiny fear is born.

00:10:38.400 --> 00:10:42.066
Total darkness always causes
at least a twinge of fear.

00:10:42.066 --> 00:10:45.467
But I, who have known only
darkness since birth have no--

00:10:45.467 --> 00:10:47.266
[GRUNTS]

00:10:47.266 --> 00:10:48.600
[GASPS]

00:10:48.600 --> 00:10:50.567
[LAUGHS]

00:10:52.200 --> 00:10:53.433
I was right.

00:10:53.433 --> 00:10:57.400
You are some kind
of demon after all,

00:10:57.400 --> 00:11:01.266
with no fear of the
dark to begin with.

00:11:01.266 --> 00:11:02.934
Then I shall attack first

00:11:02.934 --> 00:11:05.367
and not give you a chance
to feel fear.

00:11:09.166 --> 00:11:10.700
It's not over!

00:11:10.700 --> 00:11:13.133
[SHOUTS]

00:11:24.567 --> 00:11:27.000
[SHOUTS]

00:11:27.000 --> 00:11:28.867
[GRUNTING]

00:11:28.867 --> 00:11:32.300
YORUICHI:
Ichigo, we're out of time.

00:11:43.967 --> 00:11:47.667
After all that, I can't believe
that my resolve was so weak.

00:11:47.667 --> 00:11:49.467
How depressing.

00:11:51.967 --> 00:11:53.367
SHUHEI:
Whoa.

00:11:53.367 --> 00:11:56.900
That's Captain
Tosen's Emma Korogi.

00:11:56.900 --> 00:12:00.300
He must've been in trouble
if he had to use his Bankai.

00:12:00.300 --> 00:12:03.533
Whatever it is, I had better get
up there in case he needs help.

00:12:03.533 --> 00:12:05.033
YUMICHIKA:
Not so fast.

00:12:05.033 --> 00:12:08.066
You haven't finished
me off yet, you know.

00:12:08.066 --> 00:12:09.967
SHUHEI:
Who do you think you're kidding?

00:12:09.967 --> 00:12:11.300
You're beaten.

00:12:11.300 --> 00:12:14.133
YUMICHIKA:
Sorry to disappoint you,
but in Squad 11,

00:12:14.133 --> 00:12:16.333
you're not beaten
until you're dead.

00:12:16.333 --> 00:12:18.500
SHUHEI:
That's different
from Squad Nine.

00:12:18.500 --> 00:12:20.734
YUMICHIKA:
As different
as black and white.

00:12:20.734 --> 00:12:23.233
And that's why we never
give up on a fight.

00:12:23.233 --> 00:12:24.900
Maybe.

00:12:24.900 --> 00:12:26.600
But you ought to
give up on this one,

00:12:26.600 --> 00:12:28.567
because there's no way
a lowly Fifth Seat

00:12:28.567 --> 00:12:30.967
is ever going to beat
a lieutenant.

00:12:30.967 --> 00:12:33.767
YUMICHIKA:
Shall I tell
you a little secret?

00:12:33.767 --> 00:12:36.900
The only reason
I'm still a Fifth Seat

00:12:36.900 --> 00:12:40.300
is because I really don't like
the look of the number four.

00:12:40.300 --> 00:12:41.734
What do you mean?

00:12:41.734 --> 00:12:44.667
YUMICHIKA:
I think the number
three is the most attractive.

00:12:44.667 --> 00:12:48.233
But of course, Ikkaku
already has the Third Seat.

00:12:48.233 --> 00:12:49.900
So I chose the Fifth Seat,

00:12:49.900 --> 00:12:53.467
five being the closest in
resemblance to the number three.

00:12:53.467 --> 00:12:55.834
And there's more to my secret.

00:12:55.834 --> 00:13:00.600
You see, in Squad 11 we
have an unspoken agreement.

00:13:00.600 --> 00:13:02.767
We live to fight.

00:13:02.767 --> 00:13:03.967
And in keeping with that,

00:13:03.967 --> 00:13:06.000
we believe that Zanpakuto
should be used

00:13:06.000 --> 00:13:07.967
strictly for direct attacks,

00:13:07.967 --> 00:13:12.266
and that all those Kido attacks
are for idiots and cowards.

00:13:12.266 --> 00:13:16.200
Let me show you what I mean.

00:13:16.200 --> 00:13:17.700
I would imagine
that by now,

00:13:17.700 --> 00:13:21.633
you're curious about the true
power of my Zanpakuto.

00:13:21.633 --> 00:13:24.567
What I'm about to show you
is confidential, of course.

00:13:24.567 --> 00:13:28.166
My captain and Ikkaku will be
mad at me if they find out.

00:13:28.166 --> 00:13:30.166
Why, you--

00:13:30.166 --> 00:13:32.200
[RENJI GROANING]

00:13:40.734 --> 00:13:43.100
How can I still be alive?

00:13:46.567 --> 00:13:48.433
Oh, hello there.

00:13:48.433 --> 00:13:50.633
What are you doing
caring for me?

00:13:50.633 --> 00:13:52.166
RIKICHI:
I brought him here.

00:13:52.166 --> 00:13:53.734
RENJI:
Rikichi?

00:13:53.734 --> 00:13:55.433
I don't understand.

00:13:55.433 --> 00:13:58.367
They threw Hanataro in jail
for trying to help Rukia.

00:13:58.367 --> 00:14:01.166
So I thought since you
both have the same goal,

00:14:01.166 --> 00:14:03.033
he'd be willing to help you.

00:14:03.033 --> 00:14:05.500
Rikichi waited until
no one was around,

00:14:05.500 --> 00:14:07.033
and then he unlocked my cell.

00:14:07.033 --> 00:14:09.233
Thank you for helping me.

00:14:09.233 --> 00:14:11.500
HANATARO:
Actually I didn't do much.

00:14:11.500 --> 00:14:13.667
I don't know who did it,
but your wounds had already

00:14:13.667 --> 00:14:16.166
been very well treated
and bound by someone else

00:14:16.166 --> 00:14:17.300
when I got here.

00:14:17.300 --> 00:14:19.500
There's only one
who could have done it.

00:14:22.433 --> 00:14:24.367
But don't worry about that now.

00:14:24.367 --> 00:14:26.233
You just get stronger,
Lieutenant.

00:14:26.233 --> 00:14:28.667
You can count on
Ichigo to save Rukia.

00:14:28.667 --> 00:14:30.033
I just know he can do it.

00:14:30.033 --> 00:14:32.533
RIKICHI:
Yes, Lieutenant, get well.

00:14:32.533 --> 00:14:35.333
I was shocked that you
actually lost to the Ryoka.

00:14:35.333 --> 00:14:36.867
And then to make
matters worse,

00:14:36.867 --> 00:14:39.400
we learned you had broken out
of jail and disappeared.

00:14:39.400 --> 00:14:41.533
And I couldn't believe
you would raise your sword

00:14:41.533 --> 00:14:43.400
against members
of your own squad.

00:14:43.400 --> 00:14:47.133
But then I remembered
the only reason

00:14:47.133 --> 00:14:49.233
I joined Squad Six
in the first place

00:14:49.233 --> 00:14:50.800
was because you were my hero.

00:14:50.800 --> 00:14:53.867
And so no matter what happens,
I want you to live, Lieutenant,

00:14:53.867 --> 00:14:56.266
and keep on battling.

00:14:56.266 --> 00:14:58.066
I want you to be
the Lieutenant I know,

00:14:58.066 --> 00:14:59.967
who's always cool
and always fighting

00:14:59.967 --> 00:15:01.367
for what he believes in.

00:15:01.367 --> 00:15:03.100
Rikichi.

00:15:08.166 --> 00:15:10.100
TOSEN:
How can this be?

00:15:10.100 --> 00:15:13.133
He has no sense of
sight or sound or smell.

00:15:13.133 --> 00:15:16.133
He cannot sense
spiritual pressure.

00:15:16.133 --> 00:15:20.433
So then how is he
able to counter me?

00:15:22.467 --> 00:15:24.000
[KENPACHI LAUGHS]

00:15:24.000 --> 00:15:27.734
TOSEN:
Once again, he dodges a fatal
blow at the last second.

00:15:27.734 --> 00:15:31.166
[GRUNTS]

00:15:31.166 --> 00:15:32.967
TOSEN:
Every time he parries,

00:15:32.967 --> 00:15:36.467
his counterattacks
get more accurate too.

00:15:36.467 --> 00:15:40.266
Is he really a demon after all?

00:15:40.266 --> 00:15:42.233
KENPACHI:
I got a hit this time.

00:15:42.233 --> 00:15:44.734
Just a graze, but still.

00:15:44.734 --> 00:15:49.800
This Bankai that destroys
senses is a nuisance.

00:15:49.800 --> 00:15:52.834
But at least I still
have my sense of touch.

00:15:52.834 --> 00:15:55.066
And as long as I have that,

00:15:55.066 --> 00:15:58.500
I can feel the moment
his blade makes contact,

00:15:58.500 --> 00:16:01.700
then dodge and counterattack.

00:16:01.700 --> 00:16:05.633
So I know he's not going
to be able to kill me.

00:16:05.633 --> 00:16:08.300
And I'm starting to inflict
some damage on him.

00:16:08.300 --> 00:16:10.433
But this is a
boring way to fight.

00:16:10.433 --> 00:16:13.300
It's so much more
fun to cut and slash.

00:16:13.300 --> 00:16:17.100
I have to concentrate since
I can't see or hear him.

00:16:17.100 --> 00:16:20.367
And I never felt much spiritual
pressure to begin with.

00:16:20.367 --> 00:16:21.467
Damn it.

00:16:21.467 --> 00:16:23.433
Why do I have to
waste time thinking

00:16:23.433 --> 00:16:26.500
instead of just fighting him
head on?

00:16:26.500 --> 00:16:28.333
Use your instincts, Kenny!

00:16:28.333 --> 00:16:30.734
KENPACHI:
What do you think
I've been doing?

00:16:30.734 --> 00:16:33.467
Maybe you should be
using that mind-eye thing

00:16:33.467 --> 00:16:35.533
to try and visualize
your enemy, you know?

00:16:35.533 --> 00:16:36.767
KENPACHI:
If I could do that,

00:16:36.767 --> 00:16:38.533
I wouldn't be
having this problem.

00:16:38.533 --> 00:16:41.066
Let me think.
What would I do?

00:16:41.066 --> 00:16:43.333
I would give up
in a beautiful way.

00:16:43.333 --> 00:16:44.967
KENPACHI:
You'd die.

00:16:44.967 --> 00:16:46.400
Huh?

00:16:46.400 --> 00:16:48.800
That's it. That's what I'll do.

00:16:48.800 --> 00:16:52.700
Then I'll know
exactly where he is.

00:16:54.200 --> 00:16:55.900
TOSEN:
He's smiling again.

00:16:55.900 --> 00:16:59.333
Even though he's losing,
he's still enjoying the fight.

00:16:59.333 --> 00:17:02.000
You're dangerous,
Kenpachi Zaraki,

00:17:02.000 --> 00:17:05.133
far too dangerous to be allowed
to live!

00:17:07.467 --> 00:17:09.767
What? No.

00:17:09.767 --> 00:17:11.734
He didn't even dodge.

00:17:13.900 --> 00:17:15.333
Well, hello.

00:17:15.333 --> 00:17:16.867
So we meet again.

00:17:16.867 --> 00:17:18.333
Impossible.

00:17:18.333 --> 00:17:20.233
[GRUNTS]

00:17:20.233 --> 00:17:22.133
[GROANING]

00:17:22.133 --> 00:17:25.867
Now I can see you again,
and hear you.

00:17:25.867 --> 00:17:28.834
Is that just because I
have a direct hold on you?

00:17:28.834 --> 00:17:32.200
Or is it because my
body and your sword

00:17:32.200 --> 00:17:34.934
are in direct contact?

00:17:34.934 --> 00:17:37.066
Either way, it doesn't matter.

00:17:37.066 --> 00:17:39.000
Come over here
and attack me.

00:17:39.000 --> 00:17:41.033
I know your trick now.

00:17:41.033 --> 00:17:43.467
Next time, before you
even penetrate my body,

00:17:43.467 --> 00:17:45.233
I'll be able to grab your arm.

00:17:50.467 --> 00:17:52.133
TOSEN:
Damn you.

00:17:52.133 --> 00:17:53.867
I must not lose.

00:17:53.867 --> 00:17:55.900
I must destroy you.

00:17:55.900 --> 00:17:59.066
I can never lose to
the likes of you.

00:18:03.033 --> 00:18:05.734
I wish I could gather all
the clouds so they would

00:18:05.734 --> 00:18:09.467
never again obscure the light
that shines from the stars.

00:18:09.467 --> 00:18:11.967
That's beautiful.

00:18:11.967 --> 00:18:15.867
I'm going to be a Soul Reaper,
Kaname, and let justice shine.

00:18:15.867 --> 00:18:18.633
TOSEN:
But she died much too soon.

00:18:18.633 --> 00:18:21.533
If it's not enough to believe
in justice, then for her,

00:18:21.533 --> 00:18:24.066
I swear I will become
justice and seek out

00:18:24.066 --> 00:18:27.166
all the evil in this world
so that I may wipe it out,

00:18:27.166 --> 00:18:30.200
like the wind casts away
the clouds in the sky.

00:18:39.400 --> 00:18:41.667
[SHOUTING]

00:18:47.867 --> 00:18:50.066
Kaname.

00:18:50.066 --> 00:18:53.667
[TOSEN GASPING]

00:18:53.667 --> 00:18:55.934
This isn't finished.

00:18:55.934 --> 00:18:57.500
Not yet.

00:18:57.500 --> 00:18:59.800
Yes, it is. I quit.

00:18:59.800 --> 00:19:02.233
I have no interest
in fighting a man

00:19:02.233 --> 00:19:04.166
with one foot
already in the grave.

00:19:04.166 --> 00:19:05.867
I'm out of here.

00:19:05.867 --> 00:19:07.433
Dying is futile.

00:19:07.433 --> 00:19:08.867
What can a dead man do?

00:19:08.867 --> 00:19:13.066
He can't fight anymore,
that's for sure.

00:19:13.066 --> 00:19:17.533
I swear it, if it takes my
very life I will stop you.

00:19:17.533 --> 00:19:20.533
I will use every ounce
of justice in my being.

00:19:20.533 --> 00:19:23.100
What an idiot you are.

00:19:23.100 --> 00:19:25.667
If you want to die so
badly, I'll help you.

00:19:28.166 --> 00:19:29.767
Hm?

00:19:29.767 --> 00:19:31.700
No, Sajin.

00:19:31.700 --> 00:19:34.266
Don't sacrifice yourself,
Kaname.

00:19:34.266 --> 00:19:38.934
This man will never understand
your quest for justice.

00:19:40.467 --> 00:19:42.500
Sajin, I-- I.

00:19:42.500 --> 00:19:44.400
I know.

00:19:46.233 --> 00:19:48.233
So that's what's
under that basket.

00:19:48.233 --> 00:19:49.767
I always wondered.

00:19:49.767 --> 00:19:53.467
But I have to admit that it
wasn't what I was expecting.

00:19:54.900 --> 00:19:58.567
You don't seem shocked
by what you see.

00:19:58.567 --> 00:20:00.900
Outward appearances
have nothing to do

00:20:00.900 --> 00:20:02.333
with fighting abilities.

00:20:02.333 --> 00:20:04.834
The only question is if
you're beastly appearance

00:20:04.834 --> 00:20:07.967
also means you fight with a
beast's strength and tenacity.

00:20:07.967 --> 00:20:10.300
That's what matters.

00:20:10.300 --> 00:20:13.367
KOMAMURA:
You see only
what's on the surface.

00:20:13.367 --> 00:20:16.667
You have no respect for an
opponent's inner strength.

00:20:16.667 --> 00:20:18.600
That is your weakness.

00:20:18.600 --> 00:20:20.934
I am not like Kaname.

00:20:20.934 --> 00:20:23.200
I will not show
the same kindness.

00:20:23.200 --> 00:20:25.033
Bankai!

00:20:25.033 --> 00:20:27.200
[♪♪♪]

00:20:31.867 --> 00:20:35.266
Kokujo Tengen Myo'o!

00:20:35.266 --> 00:20:38.400
Now it begins in earnest,
Kenpachi Zaraki,

00:20:38.400 --> 00:20:40.867
our fight to the death--
Just the kind you love!

00:20:40.867 --> 00:20:45.500
[KENPACHI LAUGHING]

00:20:45.500 --> 00:20:47.266
A fight to the death, huh?

00:20:47.266 --> 00:20:49.934
That means I can come at
you with everything I got.

00:20:49.934 --> 00:20:52.867
And then after you're dead,
go reincarnate yourself

00:20:52.867 --> 00:20:55.967
so I can kill you
all over again!

00:21:00.700 --> 00:21:02.667
Now the time has arrived.

00:21:02.667 --> 00:21:05.800
Let us begin the execution.

00:21:17.567 --> 00:21:21.166
SUI-FENG:
It seems odd
that so few people showed up.

00:21:21.166 --> 00:21:23.066
Captains and lieutenants
from Squad One

00:21:23.066 --> 00:21:25.967
and our Squad Two are here,
plus Kuriko's Squad Eight.

00:21:25.967 --> 00:21:29.033
It's no surprise Squads
5, 11, and 12 are missing,

00:21:29.033 --> 00:21:30.266
given their casualties.

00:21:30.266 --> 00:21:32.100
And I think Zaraki's lost it.

00:21:32.100 --> 00:21:35.000
But what about all the
rest of the officers?

00:21:35.000 --> 00:21:38.133
I thought that at least Unohana
would have wanted to be here.

00:21:38.133 --> 00:21:40.734
[GASPS]

00:21:40.734 --> 00:21:42.900
[♪♪♪]

00:21:44.667 --> 00:21:46.200
[GASPS]

00:21:52.000 --> 00:21:54.000
My brother.

00:22:04.567 --> 00:22:07.867
Rukia Kuchiki, it is time.

00:22:07.867 --> 00:22:10.600
Any last words before
your execution?

00:22:14.467 --> 00:22:16.166
RUKIA:
Yes.

00:22:16.166 --> 00:22:17.934
Just one.

00:22:20.367 --> 00:22:22.533
[♪♪♪]

